# 10. Detecting Enumeration / Scanning

Attackers must scan the network first.

Evidence found:

```
172.31.37.10 making thousands of connections
```

Pattern:

```
256 attempts per port
~1900 attempts per host
```

This indicates:

```
SYN scan
```

---

# SYN Scan Explanation

Normal TCP handshake:

```
SYN
SYN-ACK
ACK
```

Scan behavior:

```
SYN sent
no final ACK
```

Purpose:

```
identify open ports without full connection
```

---

# Packet Comparison Example

Case 1 – dead host:

```
SYN
(no response)
```

Meaning:

```
host not alive
```

Case 2 – active host:

```
SYN
SYN-ACK
(no ACK)
```

Meaning:

```
port open
```

